        <article><![CDATA[<div>
<p>Review the criteria that define the weighting of attributes for the spotlight group. Based on these criteria, every record in the spotlight group is given a score. If an incident&#39;s spotlight score exceeds the spotlight group&#39;s threshold, a spotlight record is created.</p>
</div>
<div>
<p>Some criteria may be more important than others and have a higher weight. For example, the priority <strong>P3 - Moderate</strong> has a weight of 10, the priority <strong>P4 - Low</strong> has a weight of 1, and <strong>Open incidents not updated 30 days</strong> have a weight of 1000. In this example, an open P3 incident that has not been updated in 30 days has a total score of 1010 and would be prioritized above an open P4 incident that has not been updated in 30 days that has a total score of 1001.</p>
</div>]]></article>
